# Component ↔ Nix derivation naming

Every greenfield component under `components/<name>/` must use the **same** `<name>` as its
Nix derivation `pname` and flake package (`.#<name>`).

| Scope | Pattern | Example |
|-------|---------|---------|
| Component dir | `components/<name>/` | `components/libcbgeneral/` |
| Nix file | `nix/<name>.nix` | `nix/libcbgeneral.nix` |
| Flake package | `packages.<system>.<name>` | `nix build .#libcbgeneral` |
| `pname` | `<name>` | `pname = "libcbgeneral"` |

## libcb C/C++ libraries

Use `libcb<short>` (no hyphens): `libcbgeneral`, `libcbipc`, `libcbc`, …

## Build helpers

Shared build inputs are components too: `components/buildcbutils/` → `nix/buildcbutils.nix` →
`.#buildcbutils`.

## Exceptions (no `components/` tree)

Allowed without a matching directory:

- `libcb-server-libs`, `libcb-clibs` — `symlinkJoin` aggregates in `flake.nix`

Do **not** add new derivations whose `pname` diverges from `components/<pname>/`.
Do **not** add check-only wrapper derivations — put `doCheck` / `checkPhase` on the component
derivation; point `checks.*` at those same packages.
